data.description: Welcome to your dream retreat in the Texas hill country where the stars shine at night! Nestled on 2 acres, within a gated community, this magnificent Mediterranean-style home offers an unparalleled living experience with breathtaking views from every corner. For outdoor enthusiasts, the in-ground pool and spa, complemented by a summer kitchen and covered patio, provide the perfect setting for relaxation and entertainment. As you step inside, you'll be captivated by the open floor plan, high ceilings, and the warmth of the floor-to-ceiling stone fireplace in the living room, flanked by built-ins. Wood cross beams accentuate the trey ceiling, and a wall of windows internalizes the serene outdoors.  Easy maintenance ceramic tile "wood" flooring flows throughout the main living areas.   The heart of the home is the island kitchen, featuring custom cabinets, marble countertops, a farmhouse sink, stainless steel appliances, and gas cooking. Pendant lighting adds a modern touch making it a chef's dream.  There is no lack of storage in the kitchen area as well as perfect spaces for your treasured art pieces.  You will also enjoy a sit at breakfast bar and an adjacent dining area perfect for formal meals.  The area between the main living, outdoors, dining and kitchen are perfect for entertaining!  The game room, bathed in natural light and offering outside access, is ideal for leisure activities or flex space.  Additionally, you'll find two spacious secondary bedrooms and a well-appointed full bath.  On the opposite side of this split plan, you'll discover a luxurious primary suite with a wood-beamed two-tier trey ceiling, an oversized dual vanity with Cantera Stone countertop, marble flooring, a soaking tub, and a spacious walk-in shower with multiple showerheads.  The walk-in closet offers an abundance of storage with shelves to keep you organized.  There is also a spacious study for those who work from home.  The garage is generous in size and has a side entry.  Plenty of driveway for parking as well.  The yard offers so many opportunities or just simplicity.  This is a wonderful home with amazing views to come home, grab a cold beer or glass of wine, and just watch the sunsets at the end of the day.  The backyard faces north so July and August provide perfect patio weather as well.
